<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1448,2015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="439">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1809,1835]" pageId="5" pageNumber="439">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is given in honor of the biologist and colleague Dr. Dimitris Kaltsas, who contributed to the collection of the material presented here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1448,2015]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,153,539]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="440" pageId="5" pageNumber="439">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,552,1880,1907]" pageId="5" pageNumber="439">
Description. Female 
<typeStatus box="[442,547,1881,1907]" pageId="5" pageNumber="439">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Yellow spiders of medium to small size. Body and legs uniformly colored. Measurements: TL 4.965; CL 2.075; CW 1.555; AL 2.627. Eye sizes and interdistances: 
<collectionCode box="[1082,1144,1917,1943]" pageId="5" pageNumber="439">AME</collectionCode>
0.117, PME 0.092x0.119, PLE 0.107, ALE 0.123, AME-ALE almost touching, AME-AME, PME-PME and PME-PLE 
<emphasis box="[1227,1253,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="439">ca</emphasis>
equidistant and separated by less than 1/2 their diameter.All eyes round and pearly white with black surroundings, especially 
<collectionCode box="[1367,1433,1989,2015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="439">AME</collectionCode>
. PER procurved, AER straight to slightly recurved. Prosoma with widening thoracic region, fovea at posterior half of its length. Labium triangular, longer than wide. Chelicerae with 1 and 3 denticles on 
<collectingRegion box="[1147,1191,189,215]" country="Peru" name="Lima" pageId="6" pageNumber="440">RM</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectionCode box="[1247,1287,189,215]" country="USA" name="Pratt Museum" pageId="6" pageNumber="440">PM</collectionCode>
respectively. Leg formula is IV&gt;I&gt;II&gt;III. Legs spination: Leg I: Fe 2d 1pl; leg II: Fe 2d 1pl, Mt 
<date box="[1069,1099,225,251]" pageId="6" pageNumber="440">1v</date>
; leg III: Fe 4-5d, Pa 1rl, Ti/Mt spinose; leg IV: Fe 3d, Pa 1rl, Ti/Mt spinose. Preening brush at Mt III and IV, Ta densely scopulated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,153,539]" pageId="6" pageNumber="440">
Epigyne (
<figureCitation box="[309,397,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1994,2019]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,812,1975]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1418,812,1975]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. Echemus species: E. kaltsasi sp.n. (13–14), E. levyi (15–16). Left column epigynes, right column vulvae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3351030/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="440">Figs 13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[410,441,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1603,1628]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,197,1575]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,181,1583]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Echemus species: E. kaltsasi sp.n. (17–18), E. levyi (19–20). 17, 19 Epigyne. 18, 20 Vulva. AM: anterior margin, at: atrium, g: glandular head." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3351032/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="440">17</figureCitation>
). Mushroom like atrium with large cup and short base formed by lateral margins which open widely to meet anterior margin and bend medially to form the base. Sclerotized median lines also present in the atrium.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,153,539]" pageId="6" pageNumber="440">
Vulva (
<figureCitation box="[282,370,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1994,2019]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,812,1975]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1418,812,1975]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. Echemus species: E. kaltsasi sp.n. (13–14), E. levyi (15–16). Left column epigynes, right column vulvae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3351030/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="440">Figs 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[383,414,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1603,1628]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,197,1575]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,181,1583]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Echemus species: E. kaltsasi sp.n. (17–18), E. levyi (19–20). 17, 19 Epigyne. 18, 20 Vulva. AM: anterior margin, at: atrium, g: glandular head." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3351032/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="440">18</figureCitation>
). Coiled copulatory ducts with long transverse glandular heads on anterior ends. Enlarged spermathecal sacs connected to copulatory ducts and attached to anterior margin. Spermathecae of rather irregular shape (not easily distinguished in the available specimen).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,153,539]" box="[199,594,512,539]" pageId="6" pageNumber="440">
